result.execSummary:
The defendant Joel Neftali Lopez Niz was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • OWI Cause Injury (2+), a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(2)(a)1.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: In the event that the defendant is discharged from probation with outstanding financial obligations, the supervising agent SHALL notify the court 10 days prior to the revocation or discharge.  A civil judgment SHALL be entered against the defendant and in favor of restitution victims and/or governmental entities for the balance due.  All available enforcement actions will be used to collect the debt.

Any vehicles titled in the Defendant's name and/or any vehicles operated by the Defendant are subject to an ignition interlock device.  The ignition interlock requirement becomes effective when the Defendant applies for a license.

miscConds.notes: Defendant is to pay fine/costs. Defendant is to pay $30 blood draw fee.  Bond to be applied.

Defendant is to complete an alcohol assessment and comply with driver's safety plan. 

Defendant to complete AODA Assessment and all follow through.

Defendant shall provide a DNA sample. 

Defendant is to comply with any treatment/programming as deemed appropriate by the COMPAS assessment and agent.

timeConds.notes:
Defendant is to report on or before November 3, 2022 at 4:00 PM. 

Defendant may serve in Iowa if arrangements can be made with no additional costs to Trempealeau County.
